goal.core.program

Class ActionSpecification

  • java.lang.Object
    • goal.parser.ParsedObject
      • goal.core.program.ActionSpecification
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    IParsedObject, java.io.Serializable, java.lang.Comparable<ParsedObject>

    public class ActionSpecification
extends ParsedObject
    Container for an ActionSpecification. An action specification includes:
    • The name and parameters of the action (a UserSpecAction)
    • The precondition of the action that is specified (a Query), and
    • The postcondition of the action that is specified (a Update).
    An action specification is obtained from the action specification section in a module in a GOAL program. Specifications look like:
    move(X, Y) {
      pre{ clear(X), clear(Y), on(X, Z), not(on(X, Y)) }
      post{ not(on(X, Z)), on(X, Y) }
    }
    Author:
    K.Hindriks
    See Also:
